Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 1
Kepware Advanced Operations
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Data-Collector" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Kepware".
4
Move to "Advanced Operations".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
This section allows you to create Complex Array Tags. This is used to group
multiple tags that need to be sent to the cloud into a single tag. Click 'Channels' to
select a Kepware Channel from the drop down list.
None of the tags you want to group can be strings.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
6
Select the required channel from the drop-down menu.
7
Click the "Next" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
8
Select the required device from the drop-down menu.
9
Click the "Next" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
10
Click the "Start browsing" button to choose the tags from the selected Channel's
Device.
11
Click on the little "arrow" on the left to expand the folder and tick all the tags (or
folders) you want to use.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
12
Click the ">" button bewteen "Channel" and "Complex Array", after you finished
choosing the tags (or folders) you need.
13
Click the "Create complex array" button to complete the operation.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
14
When you create a complex array a special device is automatically created. You
can select it from the "CA Devices" drop-down menu to send them to the Data
Sender.
15
Click the "Next" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
16
Tick the checkbox of the device chosen previously.
17
Click the "greater than" button to move the selected device on the "Chosen" side.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
18
Click the "Next" button.
19
From the "IoT Gateway enabled" drop down menu, select the IoT Gateway that
sends the data to Thingworx.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 11
20
Click the "Next" button.
21
Click the "Add Tags" button to add the tag containing the complex array to the IoT
Gateway sending to Thingworx.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 12
22
Click on the “Finish” button and you will be given a green feedback message if
everything you have done is good.
23
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
